BEGIN:VCALENDAR
VERSION:2.0
PRODID:-//Travel Agent//EN
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Day 1 - Tokyo
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260407
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260408
DTSTAMP:20260405T185416Z
UID:5f01bf88-db54-43ac-a168-d70edb13754e@travelagent.local
DESCRIPTION:Arrive at Narita or Haneda Airport and take a private transfer
  to your luxury hotel\, The Peninsula Tokyo.\nRelax and unwind at the hote
 l’s spa\, indulging in a traditional Japanese onsen experience.\nEnjoy a
  welcome dinner at Sukiyabashi Jiro\, a world-renowned sushi restaurant\, 
 where you can savor exquisite sushi crafted by master chefs.
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Day 2 - Shibuya and Harajuku
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260408
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260409
DTSTAMP:20260405T185416Z
UID:44495ccd-0f71-4931-bd75-63ca93d2c8ab@travelagent.local
DESCRIPTION:Start your day with breakfast at the hotel\, then head to Shib
 uya Crossing\, the world's busiest pedestrian crossing.\nVisit the Shibuya
  Sky observation deck for stunning views of the city.\nExplore Harajuku’
 s Takeshita Street\, and stop by Kawaii Monster Cafe for a unique themed l
 unch.\nIn the evening\, dine at Narisawa\, a two-Michelin-star restaurant 
 known for its innovative Japanese cuisine.
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Day 3 - Akihabara and Ginza
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260409
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260410
DTSTAMP:20260405T185416Z
UID:877f6d60-72c2-417f-a65f-42284c21d95f@travelagent.local
DESCRIPTION:Spend the morning in Akihabara\, the heart of otaku culture. V
 isit the Animate Akihabara store and check out the latest anime merchandis
 e.\nEnjoy lunch at Gundam Cafe\, themed around the iconic mobile suit anim
 e.\nSpend the afternoon shopping in Ginza\, visiting luxury boutiques and 
 flagship stores.\nFor dinner\, reserve a table at GINZA KANESAKA\, a Miche
 lin-starred sushi restaurant.
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Day 4 - Odaiba and TeamLab Planets
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260410
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260411
DTSTAMP:20260405T185416Z
UID:da32b17d-88f3-409b-9fae-e1251c30acd0@travelagent.local
DESCRIPTION:Visit Odaiba\, a futuristic man-made island. Check out the tea
 mLab Borderless museum for an immersive digital art experience.\nHave lunc
 h at DiverCity Tokyo Plaza and enjoy the view of the life-sized Unicorn Gu
 ndam statue.\nSpend the afternoon at the Miraikan (National Museum of Emer
 ging Science and Innovation) to explore cutting-edge technology exhibits.\
 nDine at the upscale French restaurant\, Le Bernardin Tokyo\, for a luxuri
 ous dining experience overlooking Tokyo Bay.
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Day 5 - Asakusa and Ueno
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260411
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260412
DTSTAMP:20260405T185416Z
UID:98b90c26-d995-463c-94f9-96f24f836106@travelagent.local
DESCRIPTION:Visit Senso-ji Temple\, Tokyo’s oldest temple\, and explore 
 the charming Nakamise shopping street.\nEnjoy a traditional lunch at Asaku
 sa Imahan\, known for its delicious sukiyaki.\nSpend the afternoon in Ueno
  Park\, visiting the Tokyo National Museum and Ueno Zoo.\nDinner at Kanda\
 , a three-Michelin-star restaurant\, where you can experience exquisite ka
 iseki dining.
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Day 6 - Nakano and Ikebukuro
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260412
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260413
DTSTAMP:20260405T185416Z
UID:7d57e12b-73c6-431d-a7b3-15f52e585287@travelagent.local
DESCRIPTION:Explore Nakano Broadway\, a treasure trove for anime\, manga\,
  and collectibles.\nHave lunch at Nakano's famous ramen shop\, Ramen Jiro.
 \nHead over to Ikebukuro and visit the Pokémon Center Mega Tokyo for excl
 usive merchandise.\nDine at the luxurious Italian restaurant\, Il Ristoran
 te Niko Romito\, located in the luxury hotel\, Bvlgari Il Giardino.
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Day 7 - Day Trip to Nikko
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260413
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260414
DTSTAMP:20260405T185416Z
UID:f5f268bf-b0b5-44aa-aded-5dfee0b722ef@travelagent.local
DESCRIPTION:Take a private guided tour to Nikko\, a UNESCO World Heritage 
 Site\, known for its beautiful temples and natural scenery.\nVisit the orn
 ate Toshogu Shrine and enjoy a bento lunch at a scenic spot.\nSpend the af
 ternoon exploring the stunning landscapes of Lake Chuzenji and Kegon Falls
 .\nReturn to Tokyo and have dinner at the exclusive restaurant\, Ryugin\, 
 which offers a modern take on Japanese cuisine.
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Day 8 - Shinjuku and Roppongi
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260414
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260415
DTSTAMP:20260405T185416Z
UID:178250f5-1748-44e4-8cc5-4461b2b2b883@travelagent.local
DESCRIPTION:Visit the Tokyo Metropolitan Government Building for panoramic
  views of the city.\nEnjoy lunch at the iconic Robot Restaurant for a quir
 ky entertainment experience.\nSpend the afternoon exploring the Mori Art M
 useum in Roppongi Hills and the nearby Tokyo City View.\nIndulge in a luxu
 rious dinner at Sushi Saito\, known for serving some of the best sushi in 
 the world (reservation required).
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Day 9 - Tsukiji Outer Market and Marunouchi
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260415
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260416
DTSTAMP:20260405T185416Z
UID:9ccbe5a2-8b2f-4d21-b771-7afa5a7af3e7@travelagent.local
DESCRIPTION:Explore Tsukiji Outer Market\, sampling fresh seafood and stre
 et food delicacies.\nHave a sushi breakfast at Sushi Daiwa\, a local favor
 ite.\nSpend the afternoon in Marunouchi\, visiting the Imperial Palace and
  its gardens.\nEnjoy a farewell dinner at The Grill at The Peninsula\, fea
 turing seasonal ingredients and stunning city views.
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Day 10 - Departure from Tokyo
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260416
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260417
DTSTAMP:20260405T185416Z
UID:2d5b59a3-49bc-4eb7-bf9a-ec8b6997f5e0@travelagent.local
DESCRIPTION:Enjoy a leisurely breakfast at your hotel and some last-minute
  shopping in the nearby Marunouchi area.\nDepending on your flight time\, 
 relax at the hotel or explore the local area before your private transfer 
 to the airport for departure.
END:VEVENT
END:VCALENDAR
